==English==
===Etymology===
From '''[[Amazon]]''', a river in South America named after a group of women warriors of Greek mythology.

===Adjective===
'''Amazonian'''

# of or relating to the [[Amazon]]s; [[warlike]]
# Having to do with the [[Amazon River]] in [[South America]], and the region surrounding the river.
# of or relating to the most recent [[Martian]] [[geological]] [[time]] [[period]]

====Translations====
*[[амазонский]] (amazónskij)  (2)
===Noun===
'''Amazonian'''
# an Amazon
# the Amazonian geologocal period
